originalText.text:
Voss Events is synonymous with bringing the biggest talent, greatest production, and spectacular entertainment to the stage. I had the pleasure of attending WERK the World in Cleveland and Toronto this year. The show never disappoints. I had the time of my life! I cannot wait to catch The Night of the Living Drag Halloween Tour. This will be my third Halloween show … the first year was Drive-n-Drag and last year was in a beautiful theater. Each time feels like the first time.  I am so excited to feel the energy that every Voss Event brings!
Would highly recommend getting to a show!

originalText.text:
Went to Drive N Drag tonight at Westfield Garden State Plaza. Voss Events ran completely misleading advertising featuring twelve of my favorite queens from Ru Paul’s Drag Race. In smaller print they listed 7 queens as performing at this particular show. In fact, only 5 queens performed. The show was less than an hour, and while the queens did a good job, the event was completely underwhelming. When I emailed customer service I was met with evasiveness giving way to hostility. Then when I went on twitter to try to message the company, they had already blocked me.

Do not trust this company. They will mislead you, ignore you, and then literally block you.

originalText.text: I will never buy any tickets from this event planner ever again! Bait and switch, the event was supposed to be at another more intimate location with comfortable seating. Switched the day before event, by email to a large convention center with folding metal chairs and bleachers. Shame on Rupaul’s Drag Race! I do hope someone takes this to some type of litigation process. I purchased tickets a full year in advance, just to be told by Ticket Master that they can do what they want, sorry. I really hope others complain and spread the word about the fraud.
